===ᔒᐦᔒ (''zhiishiib'')===
<!-- It is not clear why you want to repeat this heading -->
<!-- It is repeated because first section was "zhiishiib" with the root /zhiishiib/ but this is "zhiishiib" with the root /zhiishiiby/, which in Roman letters would appear identical until you look at the syllabics.  Consequently, the first yields the diminutive "zhiishiibens" while this would yield the diminutive "zhiishiibiins".  "Zhiishiibens" is a small duck (duckling or a small adult duck) while "zhiishiibiins" is a duckling (never a small adult duck).  Consequently, "ducky" would be "zhiishiibenh" while a "baby ducky" would be "zhiishiibiinh."  In other words, the difference is sort of like the "wa" in Japanese written with は vs. わ.  CJLippert -->
